---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Solo Founder Tools - a curated directory for indie hackers and solopreneurs">
  <section class="py-12">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">About Solo Founder Tools</h1>

      <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
          A curated directory of software tools for solopreneurs, indie hackers, and one-person businesses.
        </p>

        <h2>Why This Directory?</h2>
        <p>
          When you're building a business solo, every tool choice matters. You don't have a team to evaluate options, and you can't afford to waste time on tools that don't work for your scale.
        </p>
        <p>
          This directory exists to help solo founders find the right tools faster. Every listing includes honest pros and cons, real pricing information, and relevant alternatives.
        </p>

        <h2>How We Curate</h2>
        <p>
          We focus on tools that work well for solo founders and small teams:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Reasonable pricing for individuals and small businesses</li>
          <li>Good developer/user experience</li>
          <li>Proven reliability and active development</li>
          <li>Clear documentation and support options</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Featured Listings</h2>
        <p>
          Tools marked as "Featured" have paid for prominent placement. This helps us keep the directory running. Featured status doesn't affect our honest assessment of pros and cons â€” we include those for every tool, featured or not.
        </p>

        <h2>Submit a Tool</h2>
        <p>
          Know a tool that should be listed? <a href="/submit">Submit it here</a>. We review all submissions and add tools that fit our criteria.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions, corrections, or feedback? Use our <a href="/submit">contact form</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
